content: This was a very entertaining game, for a great price! I had been wanting to play with someone for quite a while, and finally found another participant. I would have rated this five stars, but when we got to the end only player 2 was allowed to enter the clock tower, despite us both doing the sequencing correctly and even looking up if we had done anything wrong. It was upsetting we only unlocked player 2's ending, but it was still a fun little game.

My sister and I really enjoyed playing this today! We live in different states and being able to do something together was great! I wish there were 50 of these! It was beautiful and a fun way to spend a couple hours. Well worth the price. Please make more!
This was so fun! Definitely worth it.
It's short but super well-designed and worth it!

Careful! I purchased the game on my phone, then switch to tablet for a bigger screen but saw my progress was not saved, so i deleted the game on my tablet and when i got back to my phone it was also gone! Tried to install it from play store again, but was no install button only buy! So i had to buy it twice! Keep this in mind so you don't end up like me!
That wa an amazing experience!!! Thank you!
....the ending ruins the game. So offensed...
Fantastic fun experience. It's hard to find quality this engaging and interesting. Neat puzzles, interesting story, lovely artwork. Worth every penny.
Very nice game for an evening. It's a bit scary, but mostly has very tame puzzles.
Very short experience (125 mins) with 0 replayability. Puzzles were fairly easy. I don't think it's worth the $3
Far more compelling than TikTok.
good!

Excellent game! I commend the developer and creator of the game, really nailed how the story goes and the puzzle is very clever. My friend and I enjoyed it a lot. Hope you make part 2 of this. I wil definitely gonna play it!
Excellent game but short. Hope to see more games like this in the future!

*Spoiler Alert* Fairly short game but interesting. Got stuck at the last part where you have to light up specific lights to open the gate. I had been putting the right numbers on the phone and it never worked until tonight. It's either a bug or something.
It's a brilliant game. Great game for intelligent gamers.

This is like worth a 1$ game. I bought it for the two player feature, but it drags people nuts. Even tho we finished the game, but we are so frustrated during the gameplay. The puzzles are not fun, it's disgusting. We cursed hard at the end of the game. Seriously I want my money back. Word of advice, don't play this with your girlfriend or boyfriend, you will want to slap each other.

Buggy as all hell on a chromebook: - calendar jammed so I couldn't change the month until I rebooted - couldn't open the mailbox even after setting the dials correctly until I rebooted - took multiple attempts to open the clock - then couldn't open the gate at the end, despite having the same settings as my partner. Basically it was a case of solving the puzzle, banging my head against the wall, checking a walkthrough, realising the I had solved the puzzle, but the game didn't realise.

Really fun puzzle game, love the mechanics and it's a very clever way to worth with a friend to solve the puzzles without the phones actually requiring a connection. I wish it was longer though! I hope the developers make more games like this
awesome game helping inprove comunication with friends and with family library it worth it pay one time for both of u! keep doing games like this!

Took only an hour to beat. It was interesting and entertaining while it lasted. But my partner and I beat it in a little over an hour, and after considering that you have to pay for this twice to play, and on two different platforms, making the price about $10, it was not worth the price. If the game was longer sure, but this is not worth $10.
Fun little game, took us 2 hours to complete. Definitely an interesting little puzzle game.
Literally a waste of three dollars. Not worth it. Puzzles didn't work right.
Very fun puzzle game to play with a partner. Only complaint is that the game is a bit short for the price. There's lots of top notch single player escape games that are much cheaper.

If you and a friend like to solve puzzles, you really ought to try this out! You'll both need the game, and need to be able to talk to each other, either in person or over the phone. Great issues, dark and interesting story. I enjoyed all 90 minutes...
Nice, but far too short.
Creative and fun!

I wouldn't buy this game. It was really expensive with only 3 chapters. It could've been a nice experience if it weren't so short. It wasn't worth the money, that's all.
What a great little game! Its a single puzzle game, split between two screens, and there is no network required. It took us about 4 hours to play. It's definitely a lesson in communication.
A deliciously cruel game of puzzles and teamwork... my wife and i havent yelled that much at eachother for months. 10/10!
A really wonderfull experience for two people really great puzzles.
Great experience!
This was ana amazing game! well worth the money!
it's a fun game, and it's a really good way to work with one another. but I wish it had more levels. Because now that I've completed it I don't know what to do with it.
Reasonable price for the fun that we have. i wish there were more games like this
fun challenge!
Challenging escape room style multiplayer puzzles. Both players can be offline but need their own devices.

Not worth the money. Bought on Steam and then have to pay for tablet/phone app. Fantastic concept where 2 players solve together the puzzle. Good storyline, great puzzles where you need to think but game was solved in 2 hours. Very disappointed by the greedy devs. Should only have to pay for 1 device and the 2nd should be free.

It has been so hard to find a game i can play with my friend over seas. This has been such a wonderful experience for him and I to connect. Please make more games like this. We greatly look foward to it.

Innovative and clever game play. Very well done! Would definitely pay for add-on content if developers offer it. Spouse and I finished in one sitting, 90 minutes. Price felt fair since we use Google Play family services (buy once, share with another account).
This was such a unique experience to me and my friend, and aside from a couple of puzzles we weren't able to solve and had to look up, we had a great time. Fully worth the price.
Best use of co-op I've ever seen! Top 10 co-op experiences of all time!
So much fun!! Reasonable price for an hour and a half of play time. Really wish there were more co-op puzzle games out there, so thank you so much for making this!!!!
Truly excellent two-player puzzle game.

Innovative and amazing. definitely a game worth a play. I enjoyed this with my boyfriend as we love coop games. the ending was really good. what deducts from my rating is the high price. first of all, it's a relatively short game. secondly when the player is dependent on another person buying the game aswell it becomes very expensive for the amount of actual playtime. is this "double price" worth it? definitely not.
...or anyone who loves puzzles!
Great game for couples...
this was fantastic. like a mini escape room! the game does a great job of making this interactive, and the story was so clever. i hope this company has more up it's sleeve.
Fantastic .want more
Sadly unusable on galaxy S7. Decals render as solid white squares. When it rains the whole screen is covered. Hope you will fix and I will update review. 19/5/19
replyContent: Hi, thanks for letting us know about this issue! Try updating to the latest version, hopefully that will have fixed the problem. If it still persists, could you send us an email to support@othertalesinteractive ? Then we might be able to figure it out together:D

content: simple yet beautiful. brilliant game
It felt like it ended just when it was starting to really get good. Great game but way too short.
Way too short.
Great puzzles. It keeps you interested until you reach the end. I hope they make more games like this.

My husband and I play a lot of co-op games. I'm super pleased what the the complexity and love that went into this game. It's challenging at times in a good way. It's worth the money. The ending was amazing! I hope to see more games put out like this for all platforms.
Great multiplayer puzzle game. My wife and I beat it in 170 minutes. This game is lots of fun and well worth the $5 for it.
My wife and I really enjoyed this. Just wish it were longer. Please make a sequel. I've never seen a game quite like this one before.
It is great entertainment. I enjoyed it a lot. Smartly done!
Really god experience with my partner, clever enigmas, ambiance, rewarding. Really recomanded, you don't need internet perfect to play in a bus or plane! Really hope we'll get more of this :)
A game for a nice evening, worth its price.
Look, it's good. But we solved it in 128min during 5 days. So you know what you are paying for.
lots of fun, great for long distance relationships. hoping for more cooperative content like this
Really fun! I will definitely be on the look for more games like this!

I've never gotten so much value out of a $3 game! My wife and I are playing in the evenings after our son goes to bed. It's been a really fun time so far. The multi-player even works on the computer. These developers deserve your money!
really fun 2 player game! had really interesting puzzles and a great art style!
Wonderful playthough! Depending on your puzzle solving skills it can be a bit short. My wife she I made it through in two sittings, just shy of 2 hours total, but it was wonderful the whole way!
Incredible game, love the art style and gameplay! Me and my girlfriend loved it! Tick Tock 2 please!
A fun puzzler well worth the $3. must be played with a friend you get along and communicate well with.
really enjoyed it! didnt take long but was thoroughly enjoyable. would love to see more of this type of game
Had a great time with this quick puzzle game. Grab a teammate that communicates well, because it will be tested. It starts off a little easy, but does scale up. I just wished it was a little longer.
Such a great concept but it keeps crashing for me right as I solve the first puzzle. Have un- and reinstalled with no joy. Please help!
replyContent: Hi LR Parsnip, we've uploaded a new version that should fix this issue. Our apologies for the crash!

content: the game was amazing. the concept of playing two player to solve the game is genius. my only problem is that the game is very short. I hope they have some dlc or a side Story to add later. but I fully recommend this game.

EXCELLENT!!! I‚Äôm a mobile game lover and always interested in riddle games, who played The Room 1, 2 and 3 before. Tick Tock is so fresh to me to handle the connection between my mate and I, and it‚Äôs really fun!!
Relatively short, but of very high quality - perfect if you love escape rooms and collaborative puzzles!

Amazing puzzle game and concept to play with another person and solving puzzles together! The graphics and music are very suiting for the game itself and gameplay is not superhard, but very enjoyable.
brilliant experience.
brilliantly designed two player co-op!
unique two player puzzle game. lovely concept, great execution and fantastic art!
